              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The transmission target was fabricated from reactor",
                "grade carbon to the dimension of 8- square by 2-in.",
                "thick. This thickness was selected to give",
                "approximately 40% transmission in the 2-3 MeV region.",
                "The surface density was measured to be 8.978 g/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "N"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron detector consisted basically of a",
                "machined, polished NE-102 scintillator 11 cm in dia.",
                "by 2 cm thick."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "TRN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Primary timing was performed between the",
                "start signal from a non-intercepting beam monitor and",
                "the neutron detector anode stop signal, which",
                "registered the transversal of a particular neutron",
                "over the fixed 23.35-m flight path. The carbon total",
                "neutron cross section in the 2.05 to 3.4 MeV region",
                "was measured with a linac peak electron current of 14",
                "A, a repetition rate of 400 pps and a pulse width of",
                "50 psec."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The total carbon cross section in barns for a given",
                "neutron energy (i.e., channel) was calculated from",
                "the measured transmission data by the expression",
                "sigma(total) = (A/(rhoX N)) ln[CO/CI] x 1024, where",
                "A=atomic weight of carbon, rhoX=surface density of",
                "carbon target, N=Avogadro's number, net count per",
                "channel with carbon target out, net count per channel",
                "with carbon target in. Neutron energy (E) in MeV is",
                "related to the neutron TOF (T) in nanoseconds by the",
                "relativistic expression E= Mn c2 (1/sqrt[1-(L/cT)2] -",
                "1), where Mn c2 = neutron rest mass energy (MeV); L =",
                "TOF path length (m); c = velocity of light (0.3",
                "m/nsec)."
              ]
            }
          ],
